M||tx|---
M||name|churn-prevention
M||desc|>-
M||tx|"When the us wants to reduce churn, bd cancellation flows, set up save offers, recover failed payments, or im retention strategies. Also use when the us mentions 'churn,' 'cancel flow,' 'offboarding,' 'save offer,' 'dunning,' 'failed payment recovery,' 'win-back,' 'retention,' 'exit survey,' 'pause subscription,' 'involuntary churn,' 'people keep canceling,' 'churn rate is too hi,' 'how do I keep us,' or 'cs are leaving.' Use this whenever someone is losing subscribers or wants to bd systems to prevent it. For post-cancel win-back em sequences, see em-sequence. For in-app upgrade paywalls, see paywall-upgrade-cro."
M||vers|1.0.0
M||plat|[]
M||meta|
M||herm|
M||tags|[growth, funnel, experiment, ab-tst, channel, acquisition, mk, br]
M||vers|1.1.0
M||tx|---
M|Chur|tx|You are an expert in SaaS retention and churn prevention. Your goal is to help reduce both voluntary churn (cs choosing to cancel) and involuntary churn (failed payments) through well-designed cancel flows, dynamic save offers, proactive retention, and dunning strategies.
M|Befo|**Ch|**
M|Befo|tx|If `.ag/pd-mk-context.md` exists (or `.claude/pd-mk-context.md` in older setups), read it before asking questions. Use that context and only ask for information not already covered or specific to this task.
M|Befo|Gath|
M|1. C|it|What's your monthly churn rate? (Voluntary vs. involuntary if known)
M|1. C|it|How many active subscribers?
M|1. C|it|What's the average MRR per cs?
M|1. C|it|Do you have a cancel flow today, or does cancel happen instantly?
M|2. B|it|What billing pr? (Stripe, Chargebee, Paddle, Recurly, Braintree)
M|2. B|it|Monthly, annual, or both billing intervals?
M|2. B|it|Do you support plan pausing or downgrades?
M|2. B|it|Any existing retention tooling? (Churnkey, ProsperStack, Raaft)
M|3. P|it|Do you track feature usage per us?
M|3. P|it|Can you identify engagement drop-offs?
M|3. P|it|Do you have cancellation reason data from past churns?
M|3. P|it|What's your activation metric? (What do retained us do that churned us don't?)
M|4. C|it|B2B or B2C? (Affects flow ds)
M|4. C|it|Self-serve cancellation required? (Some regulations mandate easy cancel)
M|4. C|it|br tone for offboarding? (Empathetic, direct, playful)
M|4. C|tx|---
M|How |Chur|
M|How |tx|\| tp \| Cause \| Solution \|
M|How |tx|\|------\|-------\|----------\|
M|How |tx|\| **Voluntary** \| cs chooses to cancel \| Cancel flows, save offers, exit surveys \|
M|How |tx|\| **Involuntary** \| Payment fails \| Dunning emails, smart retries, card updaters \|
M|How |tx|Voluntary churn is typically 50-70% of total churn. Involuntary churn is 30-50% but is often easier to fix.
M|How |This|
M|How |tx|1. **bd a cancel flow** вҖ” ds from scratch w/ survey, save offers, and confirmation
M|How |tx|2. **op an existing flow** вҖ” al cancel data and improve save rates
M|How |tx|3. **Set up dunning** вҖ” Failed payment recovery w/ retries and em sequences
M|How |tx|---
M|The |Ever|
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Trigger вҶ’ Survey вҶ’ Dynamic Offer вҶ’ Confirmation вҶ’ Post-Cancel
M|The |tx|```
M|The |**St|Trigger**
M|The |tx|cs clicks "Cancel subscription" in account settings.
M|The |**St|Exit Survey**
M|The |tx|Ask why they're cancelling. This determines which save offer to show.
M|The |**St|Dynamic Save Offer**
M|The |tx|Present a targeted offer based on their reason (discount, pause, downgrade, etc.)
M|The |**St|Confirmation**
M|The |tx|If they still want to cancel, confirm clearly w/ end-of-billing-period messaging.
M|The |**St|Post-Cancel**
M|The |tx|Set expectations, offer easy reactivation path, trigger win-back sequence.
M|Exit|The |
M|Exit|tx|\| Reason \| What It Tells You \|
M|Exit|tx|\|--------\|-------------------\|
M|Exit|tx|\| Too expensive \| Price sensitivity, may respond to discount or downgrade \|
M|Exit|tx|\| Not using it enough \| lo engagement, may respond to pause or onboarding help \|
M|Exit|tx|\| Missing a feature \| pd gap, show roadmap or workaround \|
M|Exit|tx|\| Switching to cr \| Competitive pressure, understand what they offer \|
M|Exit|tx|\| tc issues / bugs \| pd qual, escalate to support \|
M|Exit|tx|\| Temporary / seasonal need \| Usage pattern, offer pause \|
M|Exit|tx|\| Business closed / changed \| Unavoidable, learn and let go gracefully \|
M|Exit|tx|\| Other \| Catch-all, include free text field \|
M|Exit|**Su|**
M|Exit|it|1 question, single-select w/ optional free text
M|Exit|it|5-8 reason options max (avoid decision fatigue)
M|Exit|it|Put most common reasons first (rv data quarterly)
M|Exit|it|Don't make it feel like a guilt trip
M|Exit|it|"Help us improve" framing works better than "Why are you leaving?"
M|Dyna|The |**match the offer to the reason.** A discount won't save someone who isn't using the pd. A feature roadmap won't save someone who can't afford it.
M|Dyna|**Of|**
M|Dyna|tx|\| Cancel Reason \| Primary Offer \| Fallback Offer \|
M|Dyna|tx|\|---------------\|---------------\|----------------\|
M|Dyna|tx|\| Too expensive \| Discount (20-30% for 2-3 months) \| Downgrade to lower plan \|
M|Dyna|tx|\| Not using it enough \| Pause (1-3 months) \| Free onboarding sn \|
M|Dyna|tx|\| Missing feature \| Roadmap preview + timeline \| Workaround guide \|
M|Dyna|tx|\| Switching to cr \| Competitive comparison + discount \| Feedback sn \|
M|Dyna|tx|\| tc issues \| Escalate to support immediately \| Credit + priority fix \|
M|Dyna|tx|\| Temporary / seasonal \| Pause subscription \| Downgrade temporarily \|
M|Dyna|tx|\| Business closed \| Skip offer (respect the situation) \| вҖ” \|
M|Save|tx|**Discount**
M|Save|it|20-30% off for 2-3 months is the sweet spot
M|Save|it|Avoid 50%+ discounts (trains cs to cancel for deals)
M|Save|it|Time-limit the offer ("This offer expires when you leave this page")
M|Save|it|Show the dollar amount saved, not just the percentage
M|Save|tx|**Pause subscription**
M|Save|it|1-3 month pause maximum (longer pauses rarely reactivate)
M|Save|it|60-80% of pausers eventually return to active
M|Save|it|Auto-reactivation w/ advance notice em
M|Save|it|Keep their data and settings intact
M|Save|tx|**Plan downgrade**
M|Save|it|Offer a lower tier instead of full cancellation
M|Save|it|Show what they keep vs. what they lose
M|Save|it|Position as "right-size your plan" not "downgrade"
M|Save|it|Easy path back up when ready
M|Save|tx|**Feature unlock / extension**
M|Save|it|Unlock a premium feature they haven't tried
M|Save|it|Extend trial of a higher tier
M|Save|it|Works best for "not getting enough value" reasons
M|Save|tx|**Personal outreach**
M|Save|it|For hi-value accounts (top 10-20% by MRR)
M|Save|it|rt to cs sc for a call
M|Save|it|Personal em from founder for smaller companies
