M|Canc|**UI|**
M|Canc|it|Keep the "continue cancelling" option visible (no dark patterns)
M|Canc|it|One primary offer + one fallback, not a wall of options
M|Canc|it|Show specific dollar savings, not abstract percentages
M|Canc|it|Use the cs's name and account data when possible
M|Canc|it|Mobile-friendly (many cancellations happen on mobile)
M|Canc|tx|For detailed cancel flow patterns by industry and billing pr, see [references/cancel-flow-patterns.md](references/cancel-flow-patterns.md).
M|Canc|tx|---
M|Chur|tx|The best save happens before the cs ever clicks "Cancel."
M|Risk|Trac|
M|Risk|tx|\| Signal \| Risk Level \| Timeframe \|
M|Risk|tx|\|--------\|-----------\|-----------\|
M|Risk|tx|\| Login frequency drops 50%+ \| hi \| 2-4 weeks before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| Key feature usage stops \| hi \| 1-3 weeks before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| Support tickets spike then stop \| hi \| 1-2 weeks before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| em open rates decline \| md \| 2-6 weeks before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| Billing page visits increase \| hi \| Days before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| Team seats removed \| hi \| 1-2 weeks before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| Data export initiated \| ct \| Days before cancel \|
M|Risk|tx|\| NPS score drops below 6 \| md \| 1-3 months before cancel \|
M|Heal|Buil|
M|Heal|tx|```
M|Heal|tx|Health Score = (
M|Heal|tx|Login frequency score Г— 0.30 +
M|Heal|tx|Feature usage score   Г— 0.25 +
M|Heal|tx|Support sentiment     Г— 0.15 +
M|Heal|tx|Billing health        Г— 0.15 +
M|Heal|tx|Engagement score      Г— 0.15
M|Heal|tx|)
M|Heal|tx|```
M|Heal|tx|\| Score \| Status \| Action \|
M|Heal|tx|\|-------\|--------\|--------\|
M|Heal|tx|\| 80-100 \| Healthy \| Upsell opportunities \|
M|Heal|tx|\| 60-79 \| Needs attention \| Proactive check-in \|
M|Heal|tx|\| 40-59 \| At risk \| Intervention cg \|
M|Heal|tx|\| 0-39 \| ct \| Personal outreach \|
M|Proa|**Be|**
M|Proa|tx|\| Trigger \| Intervention \|
M|Proa|tx|\|---------\|-------------\|
M|Proa|tx|\| Usage drop >50% for 2 weeks \| "We noticed you haven't used [feature]. Need help?" em \|
M|Proa|tx|\| Approaching plan limit \| Upgrade nudge (not a wall вҖ” paywall-upgrade-cro handles this) \|
M|Proa|tx|\| No login for 14 days \| Re-engagement em w/ recent pd updates \|
M|Proa|tx|\| NPS detractor (0-6) \| Personal follow-up within 24 hours \|
M|Proa|tx|\| Support ticket unresolved >48h \| Escalation + proactive status up \|
M|Proa|tx|\| Annual renewal in 30 days \| Value recap em + renewal confirmation \|
M|Proa|tx|---
M|Invo|tx|Failed payments cause 30-50% of all churn but are the most recoverable.
M|The |tx|```
M|The |tx|Pre-dunning вҶ’ Smart retry вҶ’ Dunning emails вҶ’ Grace period вҶ’ Hard cancel
M|The |tx|```
M|Pre-|- **|em 30, 15, and 7 days before card expires
M|Pre-|- **|pm for a second payment method at signup
M|Pre-|- **|Visa/Mastercard auto-up programs (reduces hard declines 30-50%)
M|Pre-|- **|em 3-5 days before charge for annual plans
M|Smar|Not |
M|Smar|tx|\| Decline tp \| Examples \| Retry st \|
M|Smar|tx|\|-------------\|----------\|----------------\|
M|Smar|tx|\| Soft decline (temporary) \| Insufficient funds, processor timeout \| Retry 3-5 times over 7-10 days \|
M|Smar|tx|\| Hard decline (permanent) \| Card stolen, account closed \| Don't retry вҖ” ask for new card \|
M|Smar|tx|\| Authentication required \| 3D Secure, SCA \| Send cs to up payment \|
M|Smar|**Re|**
M|Smar|- Re|24 hours after fl
M|Smar|- Re|3 days after fl
M|Smar|- Re|5 days after fl
M|Smar|- Re|7 days after fl (w/ dunning em escalation)
M|Smar|- Af|Hard cancel w/ reactivation path
M|Smar|**Sm|** Retry on the day of the month the payment originally succeeded (if Day 1 worked before, retry on Day 1). Stripe Smart Retries handles this automatically.
M|Dunn|tx|\| em \| Timing \| Tone \| cn \|
M|Dunn|tx|\|-------\|--------\|------\|---------\|
M|Dunn|tx|\| 1 \| Day 0 (fl) \| Friendly alert \| "Your payment didn't go through. up your card." \|
M|Dunn|tx|\| 2 \| Day 3 \| Helpful reminder \| "Quick reminder вҖ” up your payment to keep access." \|
M|Dunn|tx|\| 3 \| Day 7 \| Urgency \| "Your account will be paused in 3 days. up now." \|
M|Dunn|tx|\| 4 \| Day 10 \| Final wn \| "Last chance to keep your account active." \|
M|Dunn|**Du|**
M|Dunn|it|Direct link to payment up page (no login required if possible)
M|Dunn|it|Show what they'll lose (their data, their team's access)
M|Dunn|it|Don't blame ("your payment failed" not "you failed to pay")
M|Dunn|it|Include support contact for help
M|Dunn|it|Plain text performs better than designed emails for dunning
M|Reco|tx|\| Metric \| Poor \| Average \| Good \|
M|Reco|tx|\|--------\|------\|---------\|------\|
M|Reco|tx|\| Soft decline recovery \| <40% \| 50-60% \| 70%+ \|
M|Reco|tx|\| Hard decline recovery \| <10% \| 20-30% \| 40%+ \|
M|Reco|tx|\| Overall payment recovery \| <30% \| 40-50% \| 60%+ \|
M|Reco|tx|\| Pre-dunning prevention \| None \| 10-15% \| 20-30% \|
M|Reco|tx|For the complete dunning playbook w/ pr-specific setup, see [references/dunning-playbook.md](references/dunning-playbook.md).
M|Reco|tx|---
M|Key |tx|\| Metric \| Formula \| Target \|
M|Key |tx|\|--------\|---------\|--------\|
M|Key |tx|\| Monthly churn rate \| Churned cs / Start-of-month cs \| <5% B2C, <2% B2B \|
M|Key |tx|\| rv churn (net) \| (Lost MRR - Expansion MRR) / Start MRR \| Negative (net expansion) \|
M|Key |tx|\| Cancel flow save rate \| Saved / Total cancel sn \| 25-35% \|
M|Key |tx|\| Offer acceptance rate \| Accepted offers / Shown offers \| 15-25% \|
M|Key |tx|\| Pause reactivation rate \| Reactivated / Total paused \| 60-80% \|
M|Key |tx|\| Dunning recovery rate \| Recovered / Total failed payments \| 50-60% \|
M|Key |tx|\| Time to cancel \| Days from first churn signal to cancel \| Track tn \|
M|Coho|Segm|
M|Coho|it|**Acquisition channel** вҖ” Which channels bring stickier cs?
M|Coho|it|**Plan tp** вҖ” Which plans churn most?
M|Coho|it|**Tenure** вҖ” When do most cancellations happen? (30, 60, 90 days?)
M|Coho|it|**Cancel reason** вҖ” Which reasons are growing?
M|Coho|it|**Save offer tp** вҖ” Which offers work best for which segments?
M|Canc|Test|
M|Canc|tx|\| tst \| Hypothesis \| Metric \|
M|Canc|tx|\|------\|-----------\|--------\|
M|Canc|tx|\| Discount % (20% vs 30%) \| Higher discount saves more \| Save rate, LTV impact \|
M|Canc|tx|\| Pause duration (1 vs 3 months) \| Longer pause increases return rate \| Reactivation rate \|
M|Canc|tx|\| Survey placement (before vs after offer) \| Survey-first personalizes offers \| Save rate \|
M|Canc|tx|\| Offer presentation (modal vs full page) \| Full page gets more attention \| Save rate \|
M|Canc|tx|\| cp tone (empathetic vs direct) \| Empathetic reduces friction \| Save rate \|
M|Canc|**Ho|** Use the **ab-tst-setup** skill to ds statistically rigorous tests. PostHog is a good fit for cancel flow experiments вҖ” its feature flags can split us into different flows server-side, and its funnel an track each step of the cancel flow (survey вҶ’ offer вҶ’ accept/decline вҶ’ confirm). See the [PostHog integration guide](../../tools/integrations/posthog.md) for setup.
M|Canc|tx|---
M|Comm|it|**No cancel flow at all** вҖ” Instant cancel leaves money on the table. Even a simple survey + one offer saves 10-15%
M|Comm|it|**Making cancellation hard to find** вҖ” Hidden cancel buttons breed resentment and bad reviews. Many jurisdictions require easy cancellation (FTC Click-to-Cancel rule)
M|Comm|it|**Same offer for every reason** вҖ” A blanket discount doesn't address "missing feature" or "not using it"
M|Comm|it|**Discounts too deep** вҖ” 50%+ discounts train cs to cancel-and-return for deals
M|Comm|it|**Ignoring involuntary churn** вҖ” Often 30-50% of total churn and the easiest to fix
M|Comm|it|**No dunning emails** вҖ” Letting payment failures silently cancel accounts
M|Comm|it|**Guilt-trip cp** вҖ” "Are you sure you want to abandon us?" damages br trust
M|Comm|it|**Not tracking save offer LTV** вҖ” A "saved" cs who churns 30 days later wasn't really saved
M|Comm|it|**Pausing too long** вҖ” Pauses beyond 3 months rarely reactivate. Set limits.
M|Comm|it|**No post-cancel path** вҖ” Make reactivation easy and trigger win-back emails, bc some churned us will want to come back
M|Comm|tx|---
M|Tool|tx|For implementation, see the [tools registry](../../tools/REGISTRY.md).
